[SEP] <gen_type_start> without_reference_solution <gen_type_end> let's solve this problem using python's sympy library. <llm-code> import sympy as sp # sam hunts 6 animals sam = 6 # rob hunts half as many animals as sam rob = sam / 2 # mark hunts 1 / 3 of the total of what rob and sam hunt mark = ( rob + sam ) / 3 # peter hunts 3 times as many animals as mark does peter = 3 * mark # add all of them to get the total animals hunted total = sam + rob + mark + peter total </llm-code> <llm-code-output> 21. 0 </llm-code-output> thus they all hunt about possible \ boxed { 21 } animals in a day.
